node_6.subject: Klaus Mueller
node_6.description: This is Klaus Mueller's plan for Monday February 13: wake up and complete the morning routine at 7:00 am, go to the library at Oak Hill College at 8:00 am, spend the day writing his research paper on the effects of gentrification in low-income communities, eat lunch at 12:00 pm, continue working on his research paper, take a break for dinner at 5:00 pm at Hobbs Cafe, return to the library and continue writing until around 8:00 pm, go back to his dorm and relax before bed.
